Definition of Insertion Sort

Insertion Sort is a sorting algorithm that sorts elements by taking one element at a time and inserting it into its correct position in the already sorted part of the array.

It works similarly to arranging cards in your hand.

Algorithm of Insertion Sort
===========================
1.Start from the second element of the array.
2.Compare the current element with the previous elements.
3.Shift all greater elements one position to the right.
4.Insert the current element in its correct position.
5.Repeat until the array becomes sorted.



Python Code
===========
# insertion sort by using the two for loops
nums=[27,40,2,65,13,19]
for i in range(1,len(nums)):
    for j in range(i-1,0,-1):
        if nums[j-1]>nums[j]:
            nums[j-1],nums[j]=nums[j],nums[j-1]
print(nums)


# insertion sort by using the for and while loops
nums=[27,40,2,65,13,19]
for i in range(1,len(nums)):
    key=nums[i]
    j=i-1
    while j>=0 and nums[j]>key:
        nums[j+1]=nums[j]
        j-=1
    nums[j+1]=key
print(nums)
